lore: \b Gambler\b0. \b Spy\b0  in Jabba's Court. Has walked the palace's passageways and overheard many details of Jabba's operations on Tatooine.

lore: \b Smugglers\b0  from many worlds are hunted by the Empire for providing arms and supplies to the Alliance. The Outer Rim is their refuge.

lore: Repulsorlift skiffs are used by traders and merchants to safely cross the deserts of Tatooine. Young thrill seekers sometimes upgrade them with high-powered engines.
name: Racing Skiff

gametext: Deploy on table. Once during each of your turns, may deploy one Underworld Contacts, [Jabba's Palace] Lando, [Jabba's Palace] Leia, R2-D2, or C-3PO from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Also, while Luke is at a Jabba's Palace site, opponent's aliens there must use +1 Force to use their landspeed.
lore: "With your wisdom, I'm sure that we can work out an arrangement which will be mutually beneficial and enable us to avoid any unpleasant confrontation."
name: Seeking An Audience

gametext: Deploy on your warrior. May target a character or creature (except rancor or Sarlacc) using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Return character (and cards deployed on character) to owner's hand if destiny +1 > defense value. Creature lost if destiny +3 > defense value.
lore: Stolen Merr-Sonn blaster. Causes no permanent damage, though efficiently immobilizes its target. Effects are more severe on animals without a thick hide.
name: Stun Blaster

lore: Influence, like any commodity, has a price in the Outer Rim territories.
name: Underworld Contacts

lore: \b Smugglers\b0. Candidates who resent authority often abandon Imperial academies to sell their piloting skills to criminals. Will work for any high paying crime syndicate.

lore: Hutt \b leader\b0  of notorious criminal organization. \b Gangster\b0  of the vilest ilk. Would rather forfeit a fortune in cash than risk one whisper attesting to his mercy.

lore: Jabba runs his organization out of a palace built around a B'omarr monastery. His fortress near the border of the western Dune Sea is safe from enemies in Mos Eisley.
